P2 surface-beacon-DOP — INDEPENDENT DOP validation reference
============================================================

These fixtures upgrade the three P2 (surface-beacon-DOP service-volume) paper
GDOP claims from "Reproducible" (deterministic drift guard) to "Validated"
(the specific GDOP numbers are cross-checked against an independent computation).
They are not part of the Kshana source and are not shipped in the published
crates/packages — they exist only for the test suite. No Python is required at
test time; the reference values are committed here.

The three claims
----------------
1. satellite-count sweep (median GDOP / time-below-GDOP-6 vs N),
2. spatial GDOP map over the -70..-90 deg south-polar band (6-sat), and
3. beacon before/after GDOP table for a -80 deg south-polar user.

Oracle
------
An INDEPENDENT dilution-of-precision implementation in numpy (np.linalg.inv),
distinct from Kshana's Rust `orbit::dop` kernel (a hand-rolled 4x4 Gauss-Jordan
inversion). DOP is a deterministic function of the line-of-sight geometry alone:
each source contributes a design-matrix row [-e_x, -e_y, -e_z, 1] (unit LOS plus
clock term); the cofactor matrix is Q = (HᵀH)⁻¹ and
  GDOP = sqrt(tr Q), PDOP = sqrt(Q00+Q11+Q22), TDOP = sqrt(Q33),
with HDOP/VDOP the horizontal/vertical split of the 3x3 position block projected
onto the user's East-North-Up basis. Reproducing this numpy output for a fully-
specified geometry is a genuine external cross-check of Kshana's design-matrix
assembly, inversion and ENU projection — the same technique tests/dop_reference.rs
uses against gnss_lib_py.

Non-circular boundary
---------------------
The DOP *number* is validated against the independent numpy oracle. Only the
*geometry* (the per-source LOS unit vectors and the user's ENU basis) comes from
Kshana's own public API — legitimate and non-circular because (a) it is exactly
what tests/dop_reference.rs does, and (b) the geometry/propagation is a SEPARATE,
already-Validated claim; here the DOP for that geometry is the object under test.
Each Rust validation test additionally re-reconstructs the geometry via the public
API and asserts the LOS unit vectors match the committed fixture vectors, so a
silent geometry change is caught before the DOP comparison.

Provenance / reproducibility
----------------------------
  # 1. dump the geometry Kshana's public API produces (throwaway generator)
  cargo run --example gen_p2_independent_dop_geometry
  # 2. recompute the reference DOP from scratch in numpy and emit the CSVs
  python3 tests/fixtures/p2_independent_dop/gen_p2_independent_dop.py

The numpy per-source DOP was verified against Kshana's own dumped DOP with a max
relative difference < 1e-8 across all three configurations (dominated by the near-
singular polar-tail geometries; well-conditioned cells agree to machine precision).
The Rust tests assert agreement to a 1e-6 relative tolerance (matching
tests/dop_reference.rs).

